{"eventId":"evt_6d7e8f9a0b","eventType":"citation_replaced","claimId":"clm_spidey_003","fromRevisionId":1280000045,"toRevisionId":1280000046,"section":"Supporting Cast","before":"Mary Jane Watson-Parker was aware of Peter's secret identity from the outset of their relationship. [8]","after":"Mary Jane Watson-Parker had known Peter's secret identity since before they began dating, having witnessed Spider-Man leaving the Parker residence through her window. [8][22]","deterministicFacts":[{"fact":"New citation [22] was added referencing Amazing Spider-Man #257 (1984) where MJ reveals her prior knowledge.","detail":"Previous citation [8] only referenced their marriage era; the new citation anchors the claim with primary evidence."},{"fact":"The claim text expanded from 'was aware' to a specific event-based description.","detail":"This strengthens verifiability by citing an on-panel reveal rather than an implied assumption."}],"modelInterpretation":{"semanticChange":"Strengthened a biographical claim with primary source evidence and event-level specificity.","confidence":0.91,"policyDimension":"verifiability","discussionType":"citation_strengthening"},"layer":"observed","timestamp":"2024-04-10T08:45:55Z"}
{"eventId":"evt_7e8f9a0b1c","eventType":"revert_detected","claimId":"clm_spidey_004","fromRevisionId":1280000047,"toRevisionId":1280000048,"section":"History","before":"Following the One More Day storyline, Peter Parker's marriage to Mary Jane was erased from continuity and replaced with a long-term cohabitation arrangement preceding a mutual breakup.","after":"Following the One More Day storyline, Peter Parker's marriage to Mary Jane was erased from continuity and replaced with a long-term cohabitation arrangement preceding a mutual breakup.","deterministicFacts":[{"fact":"Revision 1280000047 was an exact revert of revision 1280000046.","detail":"User OneMoreDayWasAMistake had replaced the entire paragraph with 'The marriage was erased by a fundamentally disrespectful editorial mandate that should not be recognized as canon.' The revert was applied by moderator TrueBeliever."},{"fact":"Edit summary: 'rv vandalism — maintain NPOV per Fandom Content Policy. Editorial opinions belong on user blogs.'"}],"modelInterpretation":{"semanticChange":"Restored neutral description after editorial-opinion vandalism on a controversial retcon.","confidence":0.96,"policyDimension":"neutrality","discussionType":"edit_dispute"},"layer":"observed","timestamp":"2024-05-22T19:11:30Z"}
{"eventId":"evt_8f9a0b1c2d","eventType":"claim_softened","claimId":"clm_wolv_001","fromRevisionId":1280000049,"toRevisionId":1280000050,"section":"Origins","before":"Wolverine's origin was definitively established in the Weapon X program, where his skeleton was bonded with adamantium by Dr. Abraham Cornelius.","after":"Wolverine's modern origin was shaped by the Weapon X program, where his skeleton was bonded with adamantium—though earlier, conflicting accounts of his pre-Weapon X history exist, including the Romulus conspiracy and the Lupine retcon.","deterministicFacts":[{"fact":"The definitive phrasing 'was definitively established' was replaced with 'was shaped by' and qualified with 'conflicting accounts exist'.","detail":"Editor cited the post-Origins retcon (2006) and the Romulus arc (2009-2010) which complicated the previously clean origin narrative."},{"fact":"The editorial note 'See talk page for ongoing Romulus retcon discussion' was appended.","detail":"Indicates active editorial uncertainty about which origin elements remain canonical."}],"modelInterpretation":{"semanticChange":"Weakened the origin claim from a settled fact to a contested narrative, reflecting decades of contradictory retcons.","confidence":0.88,"discussionType":"canon_reconciliation"},"layer":"observed","timestamp":"2024-06-14T11:03:22Z"}
{"eventId":"evt_9a0b1c2d3e","eventType":"section_reorganized","claimId":null,"fromRevisionId":1280000051,"toRevisionId":1280000052,"section":"Krakoa Era","before":"(Krakoa-era content was scattered across History, Powers, and Relationships sections)","after":"(New top-level 'Krakoa Era (2019-2024)' section consolidating all content from the Jonathan Hickman to Fall of X periods)","deterministicFacts":[{"fact":"A new H2-level section was created consolidating all Spider-Man content related to the Krakoa era.","detail":"Previously Krakoa-era edits were spread across four separate sections. The consolidation was proposed on the talk page after the Fall of X event concluded in 2024."},{"fact":"The consolidation removed duplicate claims across History and Relationships sections.","detail":"Seven duplicate or near-duplicate statements about Peter's relationship with the X-Men during the Krakoa period were unified."}],"modelInterpretation":{"semanticChange":"Structural consolidation of a completed narrative era, improving navigability and reducing redundancy.","confidence":0.79,"discussionType":"structure_dispute"},"layer":"observed","timestamp":"2024-07-30T16:40:18Z"}
{"eventId":"evt_0b1c2d3e4f","eventType":"talk_thread_opened","claimId":null,"fromRevisionId":1280000053,"toRevisionId":1280000054,"section":"Talk:Wolverine","before":"","after":"Should we treat the 2024 'Wolverine: Revenge' mini-series as canon for the healing factor upper-limit discussion? It depicts Logan regenerating from a single drop of blood, which would fundamentally change the power-level section.","deterministicFacts":[{"fact":"A new talk page thread titled 'Healing factor limits — Wolverine: Revenge feat' was opened.","detail":"Thread was started by user SniktBub on 2024-08-12T20:15:44Z."},{"fact":"The thread cited the August 2024 mini-series 'Wolverine: Revenge' #1 (Jason Aaron, Marvel Comics).","detail":"The depicted feat involves regeneration from a drop of blood after complete bodily disintegration—a power level far exceeding previous canon."}],"modelInterpretation":{"semanticChange":"New source material threatens to upend established power-level consensus on Wolverine's healing factor.","confidence":0.75,"discussionType":"canon_interpretation"},"layer":"observed","timestamp":"2024-08-12T20:15:44Z"}
{"eventId":"evt_1c2d3e4f5a","eventType":"citation_replaced","claimId":"clm_wolv_002","fromRevisionId":1280000055,"toRevisionId":1280000056,"section":"Powers","before":"Wolverine's adamantium skeleton renders him virtually indestructible, with the metal being one of the strongest substances in the Marvel Universe. [31]","after":"Wolverine's adamantium skeleton renders him highly resistant to physical trauma, though the metal has been demonstrated to be destructible by sufficiently powerful forces—including by other adamantium wielders, matter manipulation, and reality warping. [31][47][48]","deterministicFacts":[{"fact":"The claim 'virtually indestructible' was replaced with 'highly resistant' and qualified with known exceptions.","detail":"Citations [47] and [48] were added referencing instances where adamantium was damaged: Magneto removing Wolverine's adamantium (X-Men #25, 1993) and the Hulk damaging adamantium constructs (World War Hulk #1, 2007)."},{"fact":"The original citation [31] was retained but the claim text was significantly weakened.","detail":"This edit followed the August 2024 talk page thread on power-level accuracy."}],"modelInterpretation":{"semanticChange":"Downgraded adamantium's durability claim from absolute to conditional, reflecting documented in-universe exceptions.","confidence":0.90,"discussionType":"power_scaling"},"layer":"model_interpretation","timestamp":"2024-09-05T13:27:41Z"}
{"eventId":"evt_2d3e4f5a6b","eventType":"claim_strengthened","claimId":"clm_spidey_005","fromRevisionId":1280000057,"toRevisionId":1280000058,"section":"Powers and Abilities","before":"Spider-Man's spider-sense provides a precognitive warning of immediate physical danger.","after":"Spider-Man's spider-sense functions as a low-level precognitive ability, alerting him to threats ranging from immediate physical danger to broader dangers including identity exposure, electronic surveillance, and even psychic intrusion—with sufficient sensitivity to detect threats hours before they manifest.","deterministicFacts":[{"fact":"The definition expanded from 'immediate physical danger' to include identity threats, surveillance, and psychic intrusion detection.","detail":"Editor cited multiple canonical sources: detecting surveillance (Amazing Spider-Man #10, 2015), resisting telepathic attacks (Spider-Man/Deadpool #50, 2019), and long-range threat sensing (Amazing Spider-Man #1, 2022)."},{"fact":"The phrase 'hours before they manifest' was added, representing a significant temporal expansion of the ability.","detail":"This claim references the 2022 Wells run where Peter sensed the Rabin threat a full day in advance."}],"modelInterpretation":{"semanticChange":"Elevated spider-sense from a combat-reaction ability to a broad-spectrum precognitive power with strategic applications.","confidence":0.85,"discussionType":"power_scaling"},"layer":"observed","timestamp":"2024-10-21T09:55:03Z"}
{"eventId":"evt_3e4f5a6b7c","eventType":"talk_reply_added","claimId":null,"fromRevisionId":1280000059,"toRevisionId":1280000060,"section":"Talk:Wolverine","before":"(Existing thread on 'Healing factor limits — Wolverine: Revenge feat')","after":"Consensus so far is that we treat Revenge as an outlier feat unless Marvel editorial confirms it's 616 canon. Counterpoint: Deadpool has regenerated from a single cell in Deadpool Kills the Marvel Universe, and that's treated as canon-adjacent alternate universe. We need an official source hierarchy statement.","deterministicFacts":[{"fact":"A reply was posted to the healing factor discussion thread summarizing the emerging consensus.","detail":"Posted by user AdamantiumArchivist on 2024-11-08T14:33:19Z."},{"fact":"The reply invokes the Deadpool equivalent feat as a precedent for how extreme regeneration feats are classified.","detail":"References Deadpool Kills the Marvel Universe (2012), an alternate-universe storyline that is not 616 canon."}],"modelInterpretation":{"semanticChange":"Editorial community leans toward classifying the feat as an outlier; consensus has not yet formalized.","confidence":0.72,"discussionType":"canon_interpretation"},"layer":"observed","timestamp":"2024-11-08T14:33:19Z"}
